12:26.733 --> 12:42.330
who is an assistant professor, I think at the time, 
maybe associate,

12:26.733 --> 12:42.330
and

12:26.733 --> 12:42.330
on the examination grade. I

12:43.752 --> 12:51.300
discussed it with them and they accepted. I said, I 
will have that paper read by And we discussed who,

12:59.116 --> 13:02.521
and I said, what about Professor Benton? Yes, he 
said, that would be appropriate. So I had

13:04.684 --> 13:08.009
Professor Benton read the paper. And Benton

13:09.471 --> 13:25.174
gave it a D. Now, I said, that is so close to the grade 
that you got, I will not change the grade. He

13:25.930 --> 13:33.038
appealed to the judicial committee, and the 
judicial committee overturned the thing without

13:25.930 --> 13:33.038
consideration. And the student judicial 
committee, and there's some faculty on it too, did

13:33.318 --> 13:41.667
not support the faculty. And I figured there are 
two problems with it. One is there's no way for

13:44.430 --> 13:49.815
faculty to appeal that kind of thing. And second, 
there's no training in the student judicial body

13:50.596 --> 13:54.300
in proper evidential procedures.

