care whether they were, some other people are 
going to write and so on, but they were both very

16:27.395 --> 16:36.830
good at what they did. Typist, this is an editorial 
note. When Gary Halter was a sophomore, he was in

16:42.039 --> 16:45.885
one of my classes, And it was my policy then, my wife 
and I would have each of my classes over to our house

16:46.304 --> 16:58.034
for a reception and to get acquainted near the end 
of the semester. And on this particular evening,

16:58.995 --> 17:14.028
this young sophomore transfer student from 
Wichita Falls, Gary Halter, stayed after

16:58.995 --> 17:14.028
everybody else left and told me he was thinking 
about dropping out of school, wasn't sure he was

16:58.995 --> 17:14.028
making much progress. Did I have any advice for 
him? We chatted a long time and I tried to persuade

17:16.696 --> 17:21.660
him that I thought he had many of the capabilities 
that a good faculty member needed. And I urged him,

17:27.159 --> 17:39.772
since he said he was short of money, go back home to 
Wichita Falls and take another year at Midwestern

17:27.159 --> 17:39.772
University that he had attended as a freshman. 
Since then, he has told me that that advice that

17:39.792 --> 17:48.181
evening was rather important to him, because at 
that point, he didn't know where else to turn. So

17:48.682 --> 17:51.445
let's add that as an editorial note here. Any other 
faculty? Yes, Arnold Bedlitz. I hired Arnold

17:55.894 --> 17:58.676
around 75. I had $9,000

17:58.876 --> 18:20.436
left in the budget, and I called down to Houston to 
